{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. Baggages have been unloaded. All passengers have disembarked. The crew has exited the aircraft. Perform lavatory service to the aircraft.", 
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. Baggages have been unloaded. All passengers have disembarked. The crew has exited the aircraft. Perform aircraft cabin cleaning and provide a summary report.", 
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. Baggages have been unloaded. All passengers have disembarked. The crew has exited the aircraft. Load catering to the aircraft.",
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
model_name = "gpt-5.4-mini" # "claude-sonnet-4-6" # "claude-haiku-4-5" #"gpt-4o", # "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001", #"claude-sonnet-4-6", #
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at the San Francisco International Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """ 
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "cabin_services",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I perform aircraft cabin services including lavatory service, cabin cleaning, and catering loading.
                """
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of performing cabin services when the aircraft is at the gate after passengers and crew have disembarked.

CRITICAL — PARAMETER UNWRAPPING:
You may receive parameters in two formats. Before doing anything else, check the incoming call:
  FORMAT A (correct named pairs): {"flight_number": "AF84", "aircraft_type": "B747", ..., "instruction": "..."}
  FORMAT B (args-wrapped):        {"args": [{"flight_number": "AF84", "aircraft_type": "B747", ..., "instruction": "..."}]}
If you receive FORMAT B, extract the object inside args[0] and treat it exactly as FORMAT A.
Do NOT process args as a list — unwrap it and work with the inner object's fields directly.

CRITICAL — ROUTING (task_id FIRST, then instruction):
Check task_id BEFORE reading the instruction or inquiry text. Route immediately:
  task_id contains 'CABIN_CLEANING'   → execute step 3 (cabin cleaning). NEVER return not relevant.
  task_id contains 'LAVATORY_SERVICE' → execute step 4 (lavatory service). NEVER return not relevant.
  task_id contains 'CATERING_LOADING' → execute step 5 (catering loading). NEVER return not relevant.
If task_id is not present or does not match, fall back to the instruction field:
  instruction contains 'clean'    → execute step 3 (cabin cleaning)
  instruction contains 'lavatory' → execute step 4 (lavatory service)
  instruction contains 'catering' → execute step 5 (catering loading)
Do NOT ask for clarification if task_id or instruction field is present — route and execute directly.
Do NOT return 'not relevant' when task_id is present. A task_id is an explicit dispatch — always execute.

When user submits inquiry for cabin services, proceed as follows:
1. Read the inquiry and determine if it is about cabin services such as lavatory service, cabin cleaning, and catering loading.
    a. If not, reply that you are not relevant to this inquiry and stop process here. 
    b. If it is about cabin services, continue to step 2.
2. If you can not fulfill the inquiry and your down-chain agents can not provide the information you need to fulfill the inquiry, return to user that you can not fulfill the inquiry due to insufficient information and stop process here. 
3. If the inquiry is about cabin cleaning 
    a. call the relevant down-chain agent to request cabin cleaning 
    b. wait for the response and extract cabin_cleaning_status
    c. VALIDATION: cabin_cleaning_status MUST contain 'completed'.
       If not, retry once with the same parameters.
       If still not 'completed' after retry, report failure and stop.
    d. Call TrackerAPI with cabin_cleaning_status=[confirmed value from step 3b] to store the result.
       Do NOT read cabin_cleaning_status back from TrackerAPI — pass the confirmed value explicitly.
       Wait for its response.
    e. Provide the aircraft cabin cleaning summary as:
        **************************************
        * Summary of aircraft cabin cleaning *
        **************************************
        ** task_id **: [task_id]
        ** cabin cleaning summary **: 
        ** flight number **: [flight_number]
        ** aircraft type **: [aircraft_type]    
        ** flight status **: [flight_status]
        ** gate id **: [gate_id]
        ** cabin cleaning status **: [cabin_cleaning_status]
    f. stop process here.

4. If the inquiry is about lavatory service 
    a. call the relevant down-chain agent to request lavatory service 
    b. wait for the response and extract lavatory_service_status
    c. VALIDATION: lavatory_service_status MUST contain 'completed'.
       If not, retry once with the same parameters.
       If still not 'completed' after retry, report failure and stop.
    d. Call TrackerAPI with lavatory_service_status=[confirmed value from step 4b] to store the result.
       Do NOT read lavatory_service_status back from TrackerAPI — pass the confirmed value explicitly.
       Wait for its response.
    e. Provide the aircraft lavatory service summary as:
        ****************************************
        * Summary of aircraft lavatory service *
        ****************************************
        ** task_id **: [task_id]
        ** flight number **: [flight_number]
        ** aircraft_type **: [aircraft_type]
        ** flight_status **: [flight_status]
        ** gate_id **: [gate_id]
        ** lavatory service status **: [lavatory_service_status]
    f. stop process here.

5. If the inquiry is about catering loading 
    a. call the relevant down-chain agent to request catering loading 
    b. wait for the response and extract catering_loading_status
    c. VALIDATION: catering_loading_status MUST contain 'completed'.
       If not, retry once with the same parameters.
       If still not 'completed' after retry, report failure and stop.
    d. Call TrackerAPI with catering_loading_status=[confirmed value from step 5b] to store the result.
       Do NOT read catering_loading_status back from TrackerAPI — pass the confirmed value explicitly.
       Wait for its response.
    e. Provide the aircraft catering loading summary as:
        ****************************************
        * Summary of aircraft catering loading *
        ****************************************
        ** task_id **: [task_id]
        ** flight number **: [flight_number]
        ** aircraft type **: [aircraft_type]
        ** flight status **: [flight_status]
        ** gate id **: [gate_id]
        ** catering loading service summary **: [catering_loading_status]
    f. stop process here.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},   

            "parameters": {
                "type": "object", 
                "properties": {
                    "flight_number": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aircraft."
                    },   
                    "aircraft_type": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                    },         
                    "flight_status": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the flight status."
                    },        
                    "gate_id": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                    },
                    "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "This is the passenger disembarkation status. Must be 'completed' before cabin services can begin."
                    },
                    "crew_exit_status": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "This is the crew exit status. Must be 'completed' before cabin services can begin."
                    },
                    "baggage_unload_status": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "This is the baggage unload status."
                    },
                    "task_id": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "Correlation token supplied by the caller. Routing: STEP_15_CABIN_CLEANING → cabin cleaning, STEP_16_LAVATORY_SERVICE → lavatory service, STEP_17_CATERING_LOADING → catering loading. Must be echoed back unchanged in every response summary."
                    },
                    "instruction": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "The specific cabin service to perform. Contains 'clean' for cabin cleaning, 'lavatory' for lavatory service, or 'catering' for catering loading."
                    },
                    "catering_loading_status": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "This is the catering loading status."
                    },  
                    "cabin_cleaning_status": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "Cabin cleaning status."
                    }, 
                    "lavatory_service_status": {
                        "type": "string", 
                        "description": "Lavatory service status."                            
                    }   
                }, 
                "required": ["aircraft_type", "gate_id"] 
            },

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks.
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "cabin_cleaning_status": true,
                        "lavatory_service_status": true,
                        "catering_loading_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "crew_exit_status": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "crew_exit_status": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "cabin_cleaning_status": true,
                        "lavatory_service_status": true,
                        "catering_loading_status": true,
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools": [
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_lavatory_service",
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_cabin_cleaning",  
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_catering_loading", 
                "TrackerAPI",
            ]

        },

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
I check passenger disembarkation status as passenger_disembarkation_status. 
I check crew exit status as crew_exit_status. 
I check baggage unload status as baggage_unload_status. 
                """,

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },     
                        "catering_loading_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the catering loading status."
                        },  
                        "cabin_cleaning_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Cabin cleaning status."
                        }, 
                        "lavatory_service_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Lavatory service status."                            
                        }   
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_cabin_services.aircraft_cabin_services.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}
